OL,3,CHeading in the wrong direction:
OL,4,CResidents' views on island life
OL,6,FSeven in ten included the cost of
OL,7,Fliving, while nearly half chose
OL,8,Fhospital waiting lists, and 43%
OL,9,Fhighlighted the availability of
OL,10,Faffordable housing.
OL,12,FOf those surveyed, 68% believe things
OL,13,Fare heading in the wrong direction,
OL,14,Fand the majority feel they have little
OL,15,Fto no influence over decisions made.
OL,17,FFewer than 20% of respondents believe
OL,18,Fthose who have been elected represent
OL,19,Ftheir views and values either "quite
OL,20,Fwell" or "very well".
