OL,3,CHeading in the wrong direction:
OL,4,CResidents' views on island life
OL,6,FLindsay Jefferies, Managing Director
OL,7,Fof Island Global Research, adds: "Two-
OL,8,Fthirds considered quality of life in
OL,9,Fthe Channel Islands as higher than it
OL,10,Fwould be in the UK.
OL,12,F"So whilst there is a clear sense of
OL,13,Ffrustration and things that people
OL,14,Fwant to change, they also recognise
OL,15,Fthat we have a good quality of life,
OL,16,Fso that is something encouraging
OL,17,Fcoming out."
OL,19,FThe full report is available to read
OL,20,Fhere.
